In this statement, President Obama commends Georgia and Governor Nathan Deal for their bipartisan effort in making the criminal justice system fairer. He highlights Georgia's latest reform bill, which covers various areas such as school discipline, correctional education for youth, criminal record accuracy, fees and fines, and occupational licensing. The President believes that this bill will improve justice and safety, setting an example for the rest of the country. He expresses hope that Georgia's progress will inspire Congress to pass a substantial criminal justice bill in the near future.